# 57_actions_align_smoke — Tier 2 m7 Align/Distribute sweep (s255).
# Validates the eight wrap-now Align/Distribute verbs migrated from raw
# `add_action` to `add_scripted_action`:
#   - Align:      align-left / align-center-h / align-right
#                 align-top / align-center-v / align-bottom
#   - Distribute: distribute-h / distribute-v
#
# Sibling smoke to 52 / 53 / 54 / 55 / 56, same conservative-shape posture.
# Largest m-batch in the sweep (8 verbs); test is correspondingly longer.
#
# **Why conservative.** No scriptable observables for align/distribute
# today. Each verb shifts the geometric position of selected objects;
# `objects` doesn't expose bounding-box / position fields. Trace
# channel: invocations land cleanly. Visual channel: Scott confirms
# menu items / toolbar popover still align identically.
#
# ── Disabled-action-fires-anyway shape (continued from m5) ────────────────
#
# Like the m5 boolean ops, all eight align/distribute verbs are
# member-stored `m_act_align_*` / `m_act_distribute_*` with a
# sensitivity pump (update_align_btn, extended in s135 m1) that
# disables them on selections of < 2 objects.
#
# Same script-can-fire-disabled-action shape as m5: invocation hits
# the canvas-side handler regardless of enabled state. The canvas
# handler m_canvas.align_selection() guards against bad input.
# Trace channel always `ok`; visual channel depends on selection.
#
# Most legible visual channel: select 3+ objects before running so
# all align AND distribute verbs have visible effect.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Eleven observables across the wrapper-side surface:
#
#   Phase 1: `list` — confirm `win` is still registered.
#   Phases 2-9: each of the eight align/distribute verbs invoked once.
#   Phases 10-11: refusal coverage.
#
# ── Caller context ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Runs through ScripterWindow's listener, m_context = RunContext::Scripter.
# All eight m7-batch verbs declare Scripter | TestRunner. Macro is OUT.
#
# ── Test isolation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Mutations to canvas state, applied in order to whatever's selected:
#
#   - `win align-left`     — selection's leftmost edges align.
#   - `win align-center-h` — selection's horizontal centers align.
#                            (After phase 2's align-left, this re-centers.)
#   - `win align-right`    — selection's right edges align.
#   - `win align-top`      — selection's top edges align.
#   - `win align-center-v` — selection's vertical centers align.
#   - `win align-bottom`   — selection's bottom edges align.
#   - `win distribute-h`   — selection's objects distribute horizontally.
#   - `win distribute-v`   — selection's objects distribute vertically.
#
# After the smoke runs: with a multi-object selection, the objects
# have been re-aligned six times then distributed both ways. Net
# effect: objects sit on a horizontal line at the same Y as the
# bottom alignment, evenly spaced horizontally and vertically. Scott
# may want ⌘Z several times to restore. Safe to run repeatedly.
#
# ── Precondition reminders ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This smoke assumes:
#   1. Curvz is running with at least one project + one document open.
#   2. For visual-channel legibility: select 3+ objects (e.g., draw three
#      rectangles, select all three). Trace channel passes regardless.

#[sub] === Phase 1: registry sanity-check — `win` is still registered ===

list

#[sub] === Phase 2: align-left verb is addressable ===

#[sub] First m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignLeft);
#[sub] visual: leftmost edges of selection align to the leftmost edge.

win align-left

#[sub] === Phase 3: align-center-h verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Second m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignCenterH);
#[sub] visual: horizontal centers align (vertical line of object centers).

win align-center-h

#[sub] === Phase 4: align-right verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Third m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignRight);
#[sub] visual: right edges align.

win align-right

#[sub] === Phase 5: align-top verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Fourth m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignTop);
#[sub] visual: top edges align.

win align-top

#[sub] === Phase 6: align-center-v verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Fifth m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignCenterV);
#[sub] visual: vertical centers align (horizontal line of object centers).

win align-center-v

#[sub] === Phase 7: align-bottom verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Sixth m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(AlignBottom);
#[sub] visual: bottom edges align.

win align-bottom

#[sub] === Phase 8: distribute-h verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Seventh m7-batch verb. Calls m_canvas.align_selection(DistributeH);
#[sub] visual: with 3+ objects, horizontal spacing equalizes.

win distribute-h

#[sub] === Phase 9: distribute-v verb is addressable ===

#[sub] Eighth and final m7-batch verb. Calls
#[sub] m_canvas.align_selection(DistributeV); visual: with 3+ objects,
#[sub] vertical spacing equalizes.

win distribute-v

#[sub] === Phase 10: unknown-verb refusal ===

win quit

#[sub] === Phase 11: extra-argument refusal ===

#[sub] Use one of the new m7 verbs for refusal coverage.

win align-left "argument"

